Merge pull request #128 from jereddanielson/master

[spec export] Change zoom-in range to 25%-400%

[spec export] Change zoom-in range to 25%-400%

It's very useful to be able to zoom in closer in the spec export without having to resort to using the browser zoom function.

This change enables zooming from 25% up to 400% in spec export by changing the scale caps. Also tweaked the zoom-in increment when zooming above to make it more natural.

Disregard this proposed change if there is some deeper reason for capping the zoom where it was, but still consider finding a way to raise it to at least 200%. 100% seems very low and I'm in favor of letting the user zoom as much or as little as they want.

Merge pull request #126 from jereddanielson/patch-2

Fixed spec value character spacing "NaN"

Fixed spec value character spacing "NaN"

msLayer.characterSpacing() can't be used directly as a value, the floatValue getter must be used instead.

This fixes the "NaN" that appears for the character spacing value in spec export.

Update: added conditional to check for null NSNumber.

Fixed spec value character spacing "NaN"

msLayer.characterSpacing() returns a NSNumber and cannot be used directly as a numerical value. Instead we have to use the floatValue getter.

This commit fixes the character spacing value in the spec export.

Display text baseLineHeight if lineHeight is zero.

lineHeight equals zero when the baseLineHeight is used, so display that instead of zero for line height.
